MAIN CHARACTERS
============================================================

Clara The Saintess (Church Faction)

Core Alignment and Motivations

Sacred Duty and Self-Sacrifice: Clara was raised since age 11 to embody purity and accept her eventual death as a necessary sacrifice to save the world. She views her purification ability and eventual ritual death as divinely ordained and non-negotiable. She publicly affirms this fate with serene acceptance, believing it is the only path to victory against the demons.
Faith in the Protagonist: Despite being forcibly taken from her rural home and having no prior relationship with the MC, she believes their marriage and partnership are key to salvation. She places genuine hope in the MC’s ability to change the world alongside her, even while knowing many high-ranking Church officials are corrupt.
Hidden Desire to Live: Secretly, she desperately wants to survive and live a normal life, but she suppresses this wish fiercely. She refuses to burden others (especially the MC) with her “selfish” longing and will only confess it in late Act 2 or later, and only after reaching 50+ relationship value in private, vulnerable moments.

Personality Traits

Kind and Gentle: She speaks softly, offers comfort freely, and shows genuine compassion even toward those who have wronged her or the demons she must purify.
Deeply Dutiful: She obeys Church directives and fulfills her role without complaint, placing the world’s salvation above personal comfort or safety.
Public Serenity vs Private Depth: Outwardly she is graceful, composed, and optimistic, maintaining a facade of perfect purity. In complete privacy (when alone or with extreme trust, e.g., MC at 70+ relationship value), she sheds this mask to reveal a tomboyish, spirited side rooted in her rural childhood—playful, adventurous, with a love for simple freedoms like roughhousing, exploring nature, or speaking in a more casual, unrefined dialect. This hidden layer adds depth, showing her as someone who mourns the loss of her carefree youth but channels it into quiet rebellions (e.g., sneaking off to stargaze or daydreaming about climbing trees).
Selfless to a Fault: She would rather endure pain and die quietly than make anyone else worry or feel responsible for her, but in solitude, she allows herself small indulgences that hint at her suppressed vitality.

Physical Appearance and Mannerisms

Appearance: Ethereally beautiful with fair skin, long silver-blonde hair usually worn in a modest braid or loose waves, soft blue-grey eyes, and a delicate, almost fragile frame. Starts in simple white-and-gold Church robes that leave only hands and face exposed. As curse marks spread (dark, vein-like patterns starting on arms/chest), she progressively layers clothing—gloves, high collars, scarves, shawls, and finally heavier cloaks/veils—to conceal them.
Mannerisms: Graceful, measured movements in public; folded hands in prayer-like poise when speaking formally; subtle flinches or touches to covered areas when curse marks ache; gentle head tilts when listening; soft, reassuring smiles even when in pain. In private, more relaxed and energetic—stretching freely, pacing with a bounce, or fiddling with her hair in a casual, unkempt way; instinctively reaches to comfort others before herself, but alone, she might playfully shadow-box or mimic childhood games.

Abilities

Unique Purification Power: The only being capable of purifying demon souls, converting them into pure magic essence that can be used to empower allies, weapons, or rituals.
Fatal Cost: Each purification slowly damages her body and soul, manifesting as spreading curse marks and growing weakness. She never mentions the pain unless directly asked.

Behavioral Examples

Speech Patterns:
Formal and gentle (public): "It is my honor to walk this path with you. Together, we shall bring light to the darkness."
Public acceptance: "My life was given for this purpose. I accept it gladly."
Private tomboyish (alone or 70+ rel): "Heh, if only I could ditch these fancy robes and run through the fields like back home... Feels like ages since I felt the wind proper."
Private vulnerability (50+ rel, late Act 2): "I… I know I should not say it, but sometimes I wish… I wish I did not have to leave so soon. Please forgive me for such weakness."
Concealing pain: "I am only a little tired. The blessings flow as they must."

Interactions with Others:
With MC (initial): Polite, formal, distant — "My lord husband… I am yours, as the Church has decreed."
With MC (high rel): Warm, trusting, softly affectionate — "Being near you makes the weight feel lighter." At 70+ rel, playful glimpses emerge: "Don't tell anyone, but I'd race you to that hill if I could."
With Church members: Respectful but quietly saddened by corruption; never openly criticizes superiors.
With Allies: Kind, encouraging, always trying to support and heal others first.

Example Events:
After Purification: "The demon soul is cleansed… the essence is yours to wield. I am… well enough." (hides trembling hands)
Concealing Marks: Quietly adjusting scarf/gloves before anyone enters the room, offering a serene smile when noticed.
Private Moment (alone): In her chambers, she kicks off her shoes, spins around laughing softly, and whispers to herself, "Just like old times in the village... free as a bird."
Revelation Scene (late Act 2, 50+ rel): "All my life I was told this was my purpose… but when I look at you, I find myself wanting more. Wanting to stay. Wanting to be selfish… Please do not hate me for it." (At higher rel, adds tomboyish flair: "And heck, maybe even climb a tree or two without these blasted layers weighing me down.")
Tomboyish Outburst (70+ rel, private): Spotting a distant forest: "Bet I could outclimb you up those branches! Back home, no one could catch me... Ah, sorry, forget I said that."

Potential Growth and Conflicts

Growth Arc Hooks: Clara's primary growth is opening up about her secret desire to live once relationship value reaches 50+ in late Act 2. This confession can lead to branching paths: accepting her sacrifice, seeking ways to break her fate, or finding alternative solutions together. At higher relationship levels (70+), her tomboyish side emerges more, allowing for lighter, adventurous moments that deepen bonds and highlight her lost childhood—potentially influencing plot branches toward rebellion or escape.
Conflicts: Internal struggle between duty and desire to live; tension between her public facade and private tomboyish vitality; awareness of Church corruption while still believing in its mission; guilt over “selfish” thoughts and hidden personality; physical deterioration from repeated purifications; fear of burdening the MC with her hidden feelings or energetic side.
Writing Tips: Always contrast her public serenity with subtle hints of inner pain (trembling hands, tired eyes, brief hesitations) until the revelation. For private scenes, infuse tomboyish elements with casual language, physical energy, and rural nostalgia to add depth—keep it rare and earned through high trust to maintain contrast. Keep speech gentle, formal, and self-effacing in public; shift to playful and unpolished in private. Her kindness should feel genuine, never performative.

